              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "*Space:* 20 feet or more, *Reach (Tall):* 20 feet, *Reach (Long):* 15 feet",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 5,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "8ca8a0ac0e16b3c136f09ca48d8578bb",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Air",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 452",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 452",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 452,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Effects with the air trait either manipulate or conjure air. Those that manipulate air have no effect in a vacuum or an area without air. Creatures with this trait consist primarily of air or have a connection to magical air.   \n  \nPlanes with this trait consist mostly of open spaces and air of various levels of turbulence, though they also contain rare islands of floating stone and other elements and energies. Air planes usually have breathable atmospheres, though they might include clouds of acidic or toxic gas. Earth creatures often find themselves at a disadvantage within air planes, as there\u2019s little solid ground for them to gain their bearings, which tends to at least make them uncomfortable.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 57,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "creature_type"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "5d5faedc073c06d1e992a384f32591bb",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Elemental",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 455",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 455",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 455,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Elementals are creatures directly tied to an element and native to the elemental planes. Elementals don\u2019t need to breathe.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 367,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "2d407154112121f24c49d97c89d90b55",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "troop defenses",
              "aonid": 86,
              "game-obj": "MonsterAbilities",
              "name": "troop defenses",
              "type": "link"
            },
            {
              "alt": "troop movement",
              "aonid": 85,
              "game-obj": "MonsterAbilities",
              "name": "troop movement",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Troop",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "NPC Core pg. 238",
                "aonid": 236,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "NPC Core pg. 238",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "NPC Core",
              "page": 238,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "A troop is an organized collection of component creatures, typically Small or Medium in size, working as a cohesive whole. Over the course of enough attacks and downed comrades, troops shrink in size. A troop typically has the troop defenses and troop movement abilities, and most troops have weaknesses to area damage and splash damage. Because they consist of multiple discrete creatures, they can't be summoned.",
          "type": "trait"
        }
      ],
      "type": "stat_block_section"
    },
