              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "concentrate",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Bullying Bluster",
          "range": {
            "range": 30,
            "subtype": "range",
            "text": "30 feet",
            "type": "stat_block_section",
            "unit": "feet"
          },
          "saving_throw": [
            {
              "dc": 30,
              "save_type": "Will",
              "subtype": "save_dc",
              "text": "DC 30 Will",
              "type": "stat_block_section"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "ability",
          "text": "The blustering gale constantly unleashes a tirade of insults and aggressive taunts. Each enemy who enters or starts their turn in the aura must succeed at a DC 30 Will save or become stupefied 1 for as long as they remain within the aura (stupefied 2 on a critical failure). The troop's members are collectively able to mimic a few curse words or insults in every language, allowing their Bullying Bluster to affect any creature who understands a language. A creature who succeeds at its save is temporarily immune for 1 hour. The blustering gale can activate or deactivate the aura with a free action, which has the concentrate trait.",
          "traits": [
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 16,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "84c09922ddd30f2144494f2cb6f19412",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Auditory",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 453,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Auditory actions and effects rely on sound. An action with the auditory trait can be successfully performed only if the creature using the action can speak or otherwise produce the required sounds. A spell or effect with the auditory trait has its effect only if the target can hear it. This applies only to sound-based parts of the effect, as determined by the GM. This is different from a sonic effect, which still affects targets who can\u2019t hear it (such as deaf targets) as long as the effect itself makes sound.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 206,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "5315505cfd3f3ba2685e9747898193b2",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Aura",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 453,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "An aura is an emanation that continually ebbs out from you, affecting creatures within a certain radius. Aura can also refer to the magical signature of an item.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 60,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "fb5f8b3d849b073e1514a6a025810470",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Emotion",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 455",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 455",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 455,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "This effect alters a creature\u2019s emotions. Effects with this trait always have the mental trait as well. Creatures with special training or that have mechanical or artificial intelligence are immune to emotion effects.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 106,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "6a1f80610baa3617c1597f49c6406313",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Mental",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 458,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "A mental effect can alter the target\u2019s mind. It has no effect on an object or a mindless creature.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 101,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "c1c0a189dd3d1a3d7c5daf9a6bafba49",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Linguistic",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 458,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "An effect with this trait depends on language comprehension. A linguistic effect that targets a creature works only if the target understands the language you are using.",
              "type": "trait"
            }
          ],
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
        {
          "ability_type": "automatic",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "Troop Defenses",
              "aonid": 44,
              "game-obj": "MonsterAbilities",
